column4:
Latinas make 55¢ to the average white man's $1! That's unacceptable.

On #LatinaEqualPayDay, I'm reminded that although we have made progress in the fight for equality, our work is far from over. 

@SenateGOP must pass the #PaycheckFairnessAct and guarantee #EqualPayforEqualWork https://t.co/4uZd8Vm4Mo

"Early estimates found that as many as 23 million Americans could be at risk of eviction by September."

@senatemajldr and @SenateGOP, do your jobs and pass the Heroes Act NOW. 

https://t.co/nTWVcEFnpa

@realDonaldTrump's response when being told by a reporter that 1000 Americans are dying daily from #COVID: 
"It is what it is."

Trump's not fit to be President.

"Along with blacks, Latinos have borne the brunt of the COVID-19 pandemic in California &amp; other parts of the U.S, becoming infected and dying at disproportionately high rates relative to their share of the population."

@senatemajldr, pass the Heroes Act.

https://t.co/eAU9QJ1uPD

Every year, more than 600 women are killed by intimate partners. 

It's been 1 year since the House passed the Violence Against Women Reauthorization Act which protects victims and survivors of domestic violence.
@senatemajldr refuses to bring this to a vote. Do your job! #VAWA https://t.co/mIaPk2FoQx

Today, the #AffordableCareAct protects the health care of over 150 million Americans.

@HouseDemocrats will ALWAYS fight to #ProtectOurCare and build upon the progress of the #ACA. 

#ForThePeople https://t.co/QdvvUE0S8y

Praying for the victims of this shooting. We have a gun violence problem in America. That's the truth.
@senatemajldr McConnell has had a bipartisan gun safety bill on his desk since last year but refuses to bring it to a vote. Do your job. #EnoughIsEnough

